<sect2 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" id="gimp-edit-paste-as">
  <title>Paste as</title>

  <para>
    This command pastes the clipboard contents. Of course, you must use
    the <quote>Copy</quote> command before, so that you have something in the
    clipboard.
  </para>
  <para>
    There is no way to empty the clipboard.
  </para>
  <para>
    The submenu offers several ways to paste the clipboard contents:
  </para>
  <para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-as-new-layer"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-as-new-layer-in-place"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-as-new-image"/></para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-float"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-float-in-place"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-into"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-edit-paste-into-in-place"/></para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="script-fu-paste-as-brush"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="script-fu-paste-as-pattern"/></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
